    </sec>
  </sec>
  <sec sec-type="conclusions" id="SEC3">
    <title>3 CONCLUSIONS</title>
    <p>With the continued growth in the volume and complexity of microarray data available via NCBI GEO, it is critical that researchers have efficient, flexible, powerful methods for querying those data. While GEO offers several options for finding microarray data, GEOmetadb provides an alternative, yet much more flexible and efficient, set of tools for both online and programmatic access to GEO metadata. We expect that improved access to GEO metadata will not only enhance researchersâ abilities to find data of interest, but also provide a possibility for users to create a customized GEO metadata database, e.g. annotating experiments with controlled vocabulary and integrating with other biological data sources.</p>
  </sec>
